Information Technology Services









Mission
Our mission is to support student, faculty and staff success by providing world class customer service, fostering faculty-led innovation and research, and enhancing operational efficiency through the effective use of information technologies.





Student Services













												Coyote One Card
					
The Coyote OneCard is your identification throughout campus.  Your Coyote One Card is available in RG-203 (Lobby).
















												FREE Software
					
CSUSB students are eligible to receive free software, including Microsoft Office 365, Portfolium, Zoom, GIS, SAS, ESET Antivirus and much more!
















												Wireless Network: Eduroam
					
Eduroam, our secure wireless network, is available to CSUSB students, faculty, staff, and visitors. Find out how to connect and much more!
















Faculty / Staff Services













												Academic Technologies
					
By offering faculty technical support and new advancements, ATI Academic Technologies stands to enhance the quality CSUSB student’s experience within the classroom.
















												Accessible Technology
					
Creating an inclusive campus environment in the classroom and work area that enables all students and employees to be successful, regardless of disability.
















												Information Security
					
Promoting the privacy, confidentiality, integrity and availability of university information resources.
















												ITS Training
					
From new employee orientation to courses in a wide variety of software, ITS Training provides hands-on workshops for faculty and staff.
















												Strategic Technology Initiatives
					
The Project Management and Assessment Office can provide project support for CSUSB Technology projects.
















												Technology Support Center
					
The Technology Support Center is the one-stop shop for your university technology needs. Our mission is to provide world-class service to students, faculty, and staff.
